48. Record number handling in PHP with suitable examples.
code:
<?php
// Array of student records
$students = array("John", "Mary", "Peter", "Lucy", "David");

// Get total number of records
$total_records = count($students);
echo "Total Records: " . $total_records . "<br>";

// Access a specific record by record number (index)
$record_no = 2; // 0-based index (so this is the 3rd record)
if (isset($students[$record_no])) {
    echo "Record at index $record_no: " . $students[$record_no];
} else {
    echo "Record not found!";
}
?>
